full_title: I Can Fix Him (No Really I Can) by Taylor Swift
title: I Can Fix Him (No Really I Can)
title_with_featured: I Can Fix Him (No Really I Can)

description.plain:
On “I Can Fix Him (No Really I Can)”, Swift attempts to “fix” her partner which she deems a “dangerous man.”

Fans theorize that this song is about Swift’s rumored relationship with Matty Healy, the British lead singer of The 1975. Healy is known for having a very “problematic” past, making numerous controversial statements prior to, and after their relationship.

Despite this, Swift felt, and believed that she really could “change” him. Although towards the end of the song, she starts to realize she cannot.

I can fix him, no, really, I can (No, really, I can)
Woah, maybe I can’t

The parenthetical format of the title may also be inspired by Healy’s frequent use of parentheses in titles, such as in “It’s Not Living (If It’s Not With You)”, “If You’re Too Shy (Let Me Know)”, and others.
